  "text": "Five Go source files under pkg/components/loki/ implement Loki client retry and timeout logic:\n\n1. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go — The core HTTP Loki client. It defines the Client interface (with Stop() and StopNow() methods) and the concrete *client struct. Key retry/timeout logic: (a) In newClient(), c.client.Timeout = cfg.Timeout sets the net/http client-level timeout from the Config. (b) In send(), context.WithTimeout(ctx, c.cfg.Timeout) applies a per-request deadline. (c) In sendBatch(), backoff := backoff.New(c.ctx, c.cfg.BackoffConfig) creates a dskit/backoff instance that drives the retry loop — it calls backoff.Wait() between attempts and checks backoff.Ongoing() to decide whether to keep retrying. (d) StopNow() cancels the context (c.cancel()), which immediately aborts any in-flight backoff.Wait() call, stopping retries without waiting for the current batch window to close.\n\n2. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go — The configuration struct for the HTTP client. It declares BackoffConfig backoff.Config (from github.com/grafana/dskit/backoff) which controls the retry back-off parameters (min/max delay, max retries), and Timeout time.Duration which is consumed by both the http.Client-level timeout and the per-request context deadline in client.go.\n\n3. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go — A fake/stub implementation of the Client interface used in tests. It implements Chan(), Stop(), and StopNow() (as a no-op). Its presence ensures test code can exercise the StopNow() contract without a real HTTP connection.\n\n4. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go — The gRPC Loki client. In grpcRetryOption() it wires up the go-grpc-middleware retry interceptor via grpcretry.UnaryClientInterceptor(grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries)), which sets the maximum number of gRPC call retries using WithMax. In timeoutCtx() it creates a context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), c.cfg.Timeout) when cfg.Timeout > 0, bounding each Push() RPC call. The import alias grpcretry refers to github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware/v2/interceptors/retry.\n\n5. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go — The configuration struct for the gRPC client. It declares Retries uint (consumed by grpcretry.WithMax) and Timeout time.Duration (consumed by timeoutCtx()), providing the two knobs that control gRPC retry count and per-call deadline."
